obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_438  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: A knockout for PKA C1 beta is used to study its role in synaptic plasticity at the mossy fiber synapse. It is shown that removal of C1 beta abolishes LTP at this synapse (figure 2 D and E).\n\nIt is well established that LTP at the mossy fiber synapse is a presynaptic process (Zalutsky & Nicoll). Additionally, it's expression does not require potentiation of presynaptic calcium influx (Kamiya et.al.). Therefore, this form of presynaptic LTP must act through potentiation of the synaptic vesicle cycle itself. The PKA substrate(s) required for LTP are unknown.. Experimental description: Generation of RIB-'- and CD /- mutant mouse lines was described previously\n(Brandon et al., 1995). Age- (lo-12 weeks) and gender matched\nmutant mice and wild-type controls were used for all experiments.\nMice were bred from heterozygous parents and then genotyped\nat weaning by genomic Southern blotting, providing wild-type and homozygous\nmutant littermates. These wild-type and mutant mice were\nthen used either for experiments or for breeding to produce additional\nexperimental mice. All mice were of the same mixed genetic background\n(C57BU6 x 129)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_438" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

